00:29:29,264 --> 00:29:32,265
how did you start looking at your game

644
00:29:32,325 --> 00:29:34,787
in terms of mechanics that add to it

645
00:29:34,867 --> 00:29:36,628
and then things that you were bringing into it?

646
00:29:36,688 --> 00:29:38,329
Like what kind of things did you start

647
00:29:38,509 --> 00:29:41,571
as like a rule set to add and subtract from your game?

648
00:29:43,220 --> 00:29:47,341
For the gadgets and stuff and heat signature, I started with teleporters because it was

649
00:29:47,421 --> 00:29:49,741
the easiest thing I could imagine to code.

650
00:29:50,402 --> 00:29:53,042
You just click where you want to go and then you change the player's position to where

651
00:29:53,062 --> 00:29:53,662
the cursor is.

652
00:29:54,363 --> 00:29:55,063
That's a teleporter.

653
00:29:56,703 --> 00:29:59,344
And then I knew that would be too powerful because the whole game is about trying to

654
00:29:59,364 --> 00:30:02,124
get to a certain location, so I came up with downsides for them.

655
00:30:03,425 --> 00:30:07,769
And actually, yeah, that was why I was planning on teleporters and I'd actually been planning

656
00:30:07,789 --> 00:30:08,429
them for a long time.

657
00:30:08,449 --> 00:30:12,573
I had this sort of document of ideas for devices and stuff and I just kept having new ideas

658
00:30:12,593 --> 00:30:13,093
for teleporters.

659
00:30:13,113 --> 00:30:15,175
I had about seven ideas for teleporters for some reason.

660
00:30:16,716 --> 00:30:22,361
And adding those in with their constraints, there's one that can only swap you with people,

661
00:30:22,421 --> 00:30:25,223
there's one that can take you wherever you want but it takes you back two seconds later,

662
00:30:26,384 --> 00:30:26,965
and then there's one...

663
00:30:27,545 --> 00:30:32,269
that can take you to anywhere that you could get to by walking anyway, instantly.

664
00:30:33,891 --> 00:30:38,054
And those all just felt really interesting to mess around with.

665
00:30:38,074 --> 00:30:39,315
So mostly it was just experimentation.

666
00:30:41,984 --> 00:30:44,986
I focus on the easiest things to make first and then see if they're any good.

667
00:30:45,387 --> 00:30:48,209
And usually they are or they need just like a small tweak to make them good.

668
00:30:49,050 --> 00:30:54,254
And so I didn't have like a big like unifying rule sets of what items could or couldn't

669
00:30:54,294 --> 00:30:54,454
be.

670
00:30:54,874 --> 00:30:57,536
What I did need to do is figure out a system for like how they're.

671
00:30:58,077 --> 00:30:59,517
programmed sort of how they're implemented.

672
00:31:00,377 --> 00:31:02,178
And so in Heat Signature, it's traits.

673
00:31:02,418 --> 00:31:03,558
Every item has a list of traits,

674
00:31:03,798 --> 00:31:05,018
and it's just a list of strings.

675
00:31:05,758 --> 00:31:08,419
The data that we save doesn't store any stats

676
00:31:08,439 --> 00:31:09,139
about the weapon at all.

677
00:31:09,499 --> 00:31:11,640
The game just knows, oh, if it's long range,

678
00:31:11,680 --> 00:31:12,860
that means it goes this far,

679
00:31:12,980 --> 00:31:14,760
and if it's silence, that means it makes this much noise.

680
00:31:15,801 --> 00:31:17,481
And that applies to like melee weapons,

681
00:31:17,541 --> 00:31:19,101
grenades, teleporters, all that stuff.

682
00:31:19,922 --> 00:31:20,702
And so that was really useful.

